akka.stream

Class BidiShape<In1,Out1,In2,Out2>

  • java.lang.Object
    • akka.stream.Shape
      • akka.stream.BidiShape<In1,Out1,In2,Out2>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, scala.Equals, scala.Product

    public final class BidiShape<In1,Out1,In2,Out2>
extends Shape
implements scala.Product, scala.Serializable
    A bidirectional flow of elements that consequently has two inputs and two outputs, arranged like this: 

    
        +------+
  In1 ~>|      |~> Out1
        | bidi |
 Out2 <~|      |<~ In2
        +------+
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
